Introduction

PENTAGON is a South Korean boy group under Cube Entertainment. The group originally had ten members and debuted on October 10, 2016, with their self-titled mini-album Pentagon. They were formed through the reality competition show Pentagon Maker, which determined the final lineup.

PENTAGON gained significant recognition with their 2018 EP Positive, particularly the title track Shine, which became a viral hit and reached number 16 on domestic music charts. Over the years, they expanded their presence in the Kpop industry and participated in Mnet's survival show Road to Kingdom in 2020.

In November 2018, member E'Dawn left the group and company following contract termination. In October 2023, Cube Entertainment announced that Yeo One, Yanan, Yuto, Kino, and Wooseok had decided not to renew their contracts, while the remaining four members extended their agreements. Despite this, all members confirmed that they would continue activities as PENTAGON.
